@startuml
' @id(USE-INIT-FORCE)
' @desc(USE-INIT-FORCE, "Re-run `mdd init --force` to overwrite every REGENERABLE scaffolding file in place without the per-file prompt: the .mdd/docs/*.md (workflow, uml-and-ocl, security-profile, deploy-profile), the workflow SKILL.md files under .claude/skills and .codex/skills, the CLAUDE.md/AGENTS.md managed blocks, and the SessionStart hook. The point is to upgrade an existing workspace to the current tool's templates in one shot. Without --force, `mdd init` keeps today's interactive per-file [o/S] conflict prompt (create when missing, prompt when present). The three accumulating STATE files (config.yml, trace.yml, approvals.yml) are NEVER overwritten by --force — they fall under USE-INIT-MIGRATE instead. Realized by SEQ-INIT-SCAFFOLD; owned by CMP-INIT-CLI + CMP-INIT-ENGINE.")
' @id(USE-INIT-MIGRATE)
' @desc(USE-INIT-MIGRATE, "On every `mdd init` (with or without --force) upgrade the three accumulating state files (config.yml, trace.yml, approvals.yml) to the current schema version WITHOUT overwriting their content. If an on-disk file's `version` is older than the tool's current schema version it is migrated in place: parsed through the current struct (so fields added since the file was written fill from their defaults), `version` bumped to current, and written back — accumulated links, approvals, and config choices preserved. If the file is already at the current version it is left byte-for-byte untouched (idempotent; keeps curated trace.yml comments). A file whose version is NEWER than the running tool is never downgraded. This is what 'updated for newer versions without being overwritten' means. Realized by SEQ-INIT-SCAFFOLD; owned by CMP-INIT-ENGINE.")
' @id(USE-INIT-RALPH)
' @desc(USE-INIT-RALPH, "Running `mdd init` scaffolds the Ralph workspace so the Ralph loop is available without any hand-created files: it registers the `mdd-ralph` workflow skill (SKILL.md under both .claude/skills and .codex/skills — a REGENERABLE file overwritten by --force like every other skill), creates the `.mdd/ralph/` directory, writes `.mdd/ralph/PROMPT.md` as a REGENERABLE per-iteration loop prompt template (overwritten by --force), and SEEDS `.mdd/ralph/PLAN.md` exactly once. PLAN.md is the SeededOnce class (DOM-INIT-SEED-ONCE): created from a starter template only when missing, and thereafter NEVER overwritten — not by a plain re-init and not by --force — and never version-migrated, because the plan is consumed-and-rewritten state that anything (the model gap, a hand-written backlog, another agent) may own. Realized by SEQ-INIT-SCAFFOLD; owned by CMP-INIT-ENGINE.")
' Objective use cases for cycle 0018 (force + migrate) and cycle 0022
' (Ralph workspace scaffolding): a one-shot template refresh (--force)
' that exempts the three accumulating state files (migrated forward) and
' the seeded-once PLAN.md (created once, never overwritten).
title MDD init — force-overwrite scaffolding + forward-migrate state (objective)

left to right direction

actor "Developer / Agent" as Dev

rectangle "mdd init" {
  usecase "Overwrite all regenerable\nscaffolding (--force)\nno per-file prompt" as Force
  usecase "Keep per-file [o/S]\nprompt (no flag)" as Prompt
  usecase "Forward-migrate state files\nconfig / trace / approvals\n(never overwrite)" as Migrate
  usecase "Scaffold the Ralph workspace\nmdd-ralph skill + PROMPT.md (regenerable)\nseed PLAN.md once (never overwrite)" as Ralph
}

Dev --> Force
Dev --> Prompt
Dev --> Migrate
Dev --> Ralph

Force ..> Prompt : <<extend>> (replaces prompt)

note bottom of Force
  USE-INIT-FORCE: --force overwrites docs, skills,
  CLAUDE.md/AGENTS.md blocks, and the SessionStart hook
  from current templates. The three state files are
  EXEMPT — they are migrated, not overwritten.
end note

note bottom of Migrate
  USE-INIT-MIGRATE: state files are upgraded only when
  on-disk version < current schema version (round-trip,
  content preserved); equal = untouched; newer = never
  downgraded. Independent of --force.
end note

note bottom of Ralph
  USE-INIT-RALPH: init seeds the Ralph workspace.
  mdd-ralph SKILL.md + .mdd/ralph/PROMPT.md are
  Regenerable (--force overwrites). .mdd/ralph/PLAN.md
  is SeededOnce: created if missing, then never
  overwritten (even by --force) and never migrated.
end note
@enduml
